                            <comment id="14705172" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 16:02:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1696812 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1696812&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1696812&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2939&quot; title=&quot;PDFRenderer.renderImageWithDPI exception with certain PDFs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2939&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2939&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: assume an empty glyph if 1 contour and -1 end point index&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14705173" author="tilman" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 16:03:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That tt font is broken according to the MS Font validator, but in a specific way: the glyph has one contour, and that one has as index of the last point -1 (read as 65535). We&apos;ll just treat this as no contours. It would be nice to hear what device/software created that PDF.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14705659" author="bjoernk" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 19:56:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for looking into this. The pdf was created with Tesseract OCR. &lt;a href=&quot;https://code.google.com/p/tesseract-ocr/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://code.google.com/p/tesseract-ocr/&lt;/a&gt; version 3.03&lt;br/&gt;
Tesseract version 3.03 creates pdf files from images and embeds the OCR text in the pdf.&lt;br/&gt;
Tesseract 3.03 ships e.g. with Ubuntu (apt get install tesseract-ocr). It&apos;s quite handy because it lets you create OCR&apos;rd pdf files from the command line.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14705709" author="tilman" created="Thu, 20 Aug 2015 20:33:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks. I found the place where the font is created (GlyphLessFont.c), and I couldn&apos;t find the place where the wrong ffff is created. However, there is a comment &quot;Significant change to invisible font system&quot; suggesting that it had been changed recently, so I won&apos;t raise the problem there for now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
